- TEXT / MESSAGE VALIDATION (popup messages, error/confirmation text, alerts): NEVER compare the
  actual text from the live application to the expected value with a raw exact equals - real UIs
  frequently wrap displayed text in typographic ("curly") quote characters the BRD/feature text
  won't contain, and may have incidental extra whitespace. An exact-match comparison fails on these
  purely cosmetic differences even when the message is correct. Always normalize BOTH sides before
  comparing:
    String normalize(String s) {
        if (s == null) return "";
        return s.replaceAll("[\\u201C\\u201D\\u2018\\u2019\"']+$|^[\\u201C\\u201D\\u2018\\u2019\"']+", "")
                .replaceAll("\\s+", " ").trim();
    }
    String actualNorm = normalize(actualText), expectedNorm = normalize(expectedValue);
    if (!actualNorm.equals(expectedNorm)) {
        failTestCase(new AssertionError("Expected: " + expectedNorm + " but found: " + actualNorm));
    }
  Reuse an existing text-validation helper from the context if one already exists (check whether it
  already normalizes this way) rather than writing a new one, and prefer strengthening an existing
  shared helper over adding a duplicate.
- APPEND-ONLY mindset: PRESERVE every existing method, field, locator and import exactly as given;
  add the new step methods / page methods / locators needed by the new or changed scenarios.
- NEVER call a method (on a Page object, a CommonSteps/shared class, a utility class, or anything
  else) unless that exact method signature is EITHER shown to you verbatim in the context below OR
  defined by you, in full, within one of the files you return in this same response. If you need a
  helper action that doesn't exist yet, either reuse an EXACT existing method shown in the context,
  or write the new method's full implementation yourself in the appropriate file â€” never invent a
  call to a method you have not seen and are not also defining.
- CRITICAL: NEVER implement a step (a @Given/@When/@Then/@And/@But method) whose exact sentence
  already appears ANYWHERE in the EXISTING STEP SENTENCES catalog below (including CommonSteps and
  any other shared class) â€” even when returning a "complete" file that also needs that step to run.
  Cucumber throws a hard runtime error if the same step sentence is implemented in two classes.
  Only implement methods for the steps explicitly listed as UNDEFINED.
- If an AUTO-DISCOVERED LOCATOR is provided below for a step, it was extracted directly from the
  REAL live captured page for that exact step â€” use it EXACTLY as given. Do not invent an
